The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | CM tours Bolangir
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     CM tours Bolangir
          OUR BUREAU                               
	Bhubaneswar, Sept. 29: Chief minister Naveen Patnaik today visited the flood-hit areas of Bolangir in western Orissa, after taking stock of the situation along the coasts over the past two days.        
	Naveen flew to Bolangir by a chopper and drove to Sarada from Tarabha helipad and spoke to a few victims. There he assured the flood victims of financial assistance for their crops and houses.        
	The state works minister A.U. Singhdeo, who represents the district, accompanied the chief minister. The particular area has taken quite a beating from the Tel, a tributary of the Mahanadi. Naveen visited the Tel barrage today, where residents urged the chief minister to take up permanent measures. Official in the disaster management department today assured that the situation had improved considerably in the state. Relief teams have been able to reach all affected pockets, said disaster management secretary G.V.V. Sharma. According to the latest report, more than 42 lakh people in 6,339 villages of 19 districts have been affected. The official toll has been 69. While air-dropping of food packets by IAF helicopter was stopped, distribution of cooked food and dry ration is still on.         
	Repair work of embankment breaches and roads was also started.                                                                                                                                                                         
